the majority of radiosurgery patients have benign tumors or arteriovenous 
malformations and their life expectancy is long, all doses should be kept as low 
as reasonably achievable. This could be accomplished by the use of modern 
irradiation techniques including conformal beams with micro-multileaf collimator 
and avoiding beams directed to the trunk.

