not reachable. Life expectancy in basic group was 3.5 years and average HHS in 
examined group was 72,06 points. Our study showed that unipolar partial hip 
endoprothesis implanted after femoral neck fracture achieves long term fair 
clinical result. Main factor on a patient's recovery is not type of implanted 
hip endoprothesis, but general health condition before injury, motivation and 
early postoperative mobilization.

